    <title>Tate resolutions on toric varieties</title>
    <summary>  We develop an analogue of Eisenbud-Floystad-Schreyer's Tate resolutions for
toric varieties. Our construction, which is given by a noncommutative analogue
of a Fourier-Mukai transform, works quite generally and provides a new
perspective on the relationship between Tate resolutions and Beilinson's
resolution of the diagonal. We also develop a Beilinson-type resolution of the
diagonal for toric varieties and use it to generalize
Eisenbud-Floystad-Schreyer's computationally effective construction of
Beilinson monads.
</summary>
